12th-14th December, 1901

A torrid period of weather down in Kent, eastern & southern England. At Margate around 25mm's of rain fell, a daily record on the 12th with strong winds and dark skies. London, Oxford, Dungeness & Yarmouth all had heavy rain, strong winds & gales too!
